From 00921f22ff9a8792d7663ef8fadd4823402a6324 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Timothy Bish <tabish121@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 13 Aug 2014 11:15:29 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Remove unused ConnectionControl handling.


diff --git a/activemq-broker/src/main/java/org/apache/activemq/broker/TransportConnection.java b/activemq-broker/src/main/java/org/apache/activemq/broker/TransportConnection.java
index 22a63b8cf..5bb7ec1ec 100755
--- a/activemq-broker/src/main/java/org/apache/activemq/broker/TransportConnection.java
+++ b/activemq-broker/src/main/java/org/apache/activemq/broker/TransportConnection.java
@@ -1534,10 +1534,6 @@ public class TransportConnection implements Connection, Task, CommandVisitor {

     @Override
     public Response processControlCommand(ControlCommand command) throws Exception {
-        String control = command.getCommand();
-        if (control != null && control.equals("shutdown")) {
-            System.exit(0);
-        }
         return null;
     }

-- 
2.34.1

The code statements that lead to the bug are:
```java
String control = command.getCommand();
if (control != null && control.equals("shutdown")) {
    System.exit(0);
}
```
Reason:
The presence of this code allows for the application to terminate unexpectedly if the "shutdown" command is invoked, which is unnecessary and could lead to unintended behavior.

The code statements that fix the bug are:
```java
// Removed the shutdown handling code
```
Reason:
By removing the unused code that handles the "shutdown" command, the risk of the application terminating unexpectedly is eliminated, simplifying the control command processing logic.

